The paper discusses the Histogram of Oriented Gradient (HOG) descriptor, which is commonly used in computer vision applications such as image classification and object detection. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses differentiable rendering and optimization, which suggests that it may also belong to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.GR (Graphics). Finally, the paper discusses pose estimation, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category cs.RO (Robotics).
